    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I wrote a quick test to see if `privateFor` was at least past down to the provider. It turns out, in certain cases it was: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/pull/1940\r\n\r\nFrom what I've found, if a parameter that web3 expects is added to the transaction options (like `from`) then `privateFor` is accepted and past down. Without `from` it'll be ignored.",
