    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Chiming in because I didn't capture it well on the original ticket, but it's also worth pointing out the existence of `eth_sendRawPrivateTransacton`, which is analogous to `eth_sendRawTransaction`, but intended for use with, as you likely guessed by now, private transactions.\r\n\r\nThis means that when signing a transaction, `truffle-hdwallet-provider` and similar signing providers should check for the existence of the `privateFor` field and use `eth_sendRawPrivateTransaction` with the signing techinque described in the quorum docs [here](https://github.com/jpmorganchase/quorum/blob/master/docs/api.md#ethsendrawprivatetransaction) (other RPC API modifications are detailed [on the same page](https://github.com/jpmorganchase/quorum/blob/master/docs/api.md)).\r\n\r\nAlso for completeness, here's a link to the docs on [how quorum processes private transactions](https://github.com/jpmorganchase/quorum/wiki/Transaction-Processing#private-transactions)\r\n\r\nJust wanted to make sure the information was captured, so no worries if you decide this is out of scope for this ticket ;-)",
